{"title":"22.2 Ain’t Dead! A Look at the Paul Component Engineering 22.2 Boxcar 6-Bolt Face Stem – john watson","link":"https://theradavist.com/paul-22-2-boxcar-6-bolt-face-stem-review/","date":1697806202000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-1.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-1.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-1.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-1.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-1.jpg?resize=1800,1201&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-1.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-1.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-1.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><em>⌀22.2mm or 7/8″ bars were all they had back during the genesis of the almighty MOUNTAINBIKE. Riders would take the entire cockpit off their dirtbikes and flat track racers: Magura L363.20 bars, Magura brake/clutch levers, and even Magura grips, mounting them to SR or Cinelli quill stems. A lot has changed since the late 1970s but one thing remains: people love these small-diameter clamp bars for their mountain cruisers, klunkers, hardtails, and rigid MTBs. You know, the bikes that get ridden super hard!</em></p>\n<p><em>Paul Component Engineering offers their normal Boxcar stem in a ⌀22.2mm clamp, but today they announced a <a href=\"https://www.paulcomp.com/shop/components/cockpit/22-2-ltd-boxcar/\" target=\"_blank\">6-bolt faceplate Boxcar Limited stem</a> (<span><bdi><span>$</span>147.50</bdi></span> – <span><bdi><span>$</span>166.50)</bdi></span>. </em></p>\n<p><em>John got his hands on one before the drop and has some photos and thoughts below…</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-8.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-8.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-8.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-8.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-8.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-8.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-8.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-8.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-5.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-5.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-5.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-5.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-5.jpg?resize=1800,1201&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-5.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-5.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-5.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><em>Standard ⌀22.2 Boxcar on the left, limited edition 6-bolt faceplate ⌀22.2 Boxcar, right.</em></p>\n<h3>Limited Boxcar Stem</h3>\n<p>So why the extra two bolts? Well, the answer is easy: why not? Why not make a faceplate a little bit stronger for those riders who like ⌀22.2 bars? Especially when you’re torquing down some 850mm wide DOOM bars! That’s the thing with ⌀22.2 bars; most are very wide. PAUL doesn’t have an issue with its 4-bolt faceplates but they thought it’d be fun to up the ante a bit more and beefen up the connection between the Boxcar and these wide-ass barz.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-4.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-4.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-4.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-4.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-4.jpg?resize=1800,1201&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-4.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-4.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-4.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>PAUL already uses 2024 alloy for its Boxcar stems. This particular aluminum has a higher fatigue and yield strength than 6061. Then, PAUL. made sure the clamp was extra thick in the 6-bolt design. Is all this effort and engineering overkill? Definitely.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-3.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-3.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-3.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-3.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-3.jpg?resize=1800,1201&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-3.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-3.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-3.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>To keep it niche, PAUL makes this stem in 35mm and 50mm lengths; i.e. the ideal extension for mountain bike riding. These are 0º rise stems.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-2.jpg?fit=1024,9999&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-2.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-2.jpg?resize=1024,683&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-2.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-2.jpg?resize=1800,1201&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-2.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-2.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/10/PAUL-Boxcar-22.2-Stem-Review-2.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>As you can see, ⌀22.2 bars and this new, 6-bolt Boxcar stem can drastically transform the look of any bike. Including a cargo bike! More on that later…</p>\n<p>This is why I love small makers. They can sense a demand for a niche product, for a niche community, and after some CAD work, machining work, and testing, they’ve got a super fun product you didn’t think you needed.</p>\n<p><strong>Specs:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Material: 2024 Aluminum</li>\n<li><span><bdi><span>Price $</span>147.50</bdi></span> – <span><bdi><span>$</span>166.50</bdi></span></li>\n<li>Weight: 180-210g</li>\n<li>Finish: Anodized or Polished</li>\n<li>Anodized Colors: Black, Purple, Silver or Pewter</li>\n<li>Clamp Diameter: 7/8” (⌀22.2mm)</li>\n<li>Machined by the lovely team at PAUL in sunny Chico, California</li>\n<li>In stock: NOW</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Check out more at <a href=\"https://www.paulcomp.com/shop/components/cockpit/22-2-ltd-boxcar/\" target=\"_blank\">PAUL</a>.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/paul-22-2-boxcar-6-bolt-face-stem-review/\">22.2 Ain’t Dead! A Look at the Paul Component Engineering 22.2 Boxcar 6-Bolt Face Stem</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"a225cf5f3d2929294244f219281ad0e0ad70fde0e71c73dd00fbe1530be3030d","category":"Cycling"}